condition.narrative: Cote d'Ivoire: Finance Agreement: Prepare an annual work plan | Description: The Recipient shall each calendar year, prepare, incooperation with the Participating Universities and furnish to the Association, a program of activities and budget. | Frequency:Yearly

Cote d'Ivoire: Finance Agreement: Recruitment of an external auditor | Description :(applicable to all countries). The Recipientshall, not later than six months after the Effective Date, recruit an external independent auditor, under terms of reference andwith qualifications acceptable to the Bank.

Cote d'Ivoire: Finance Agreement: Regular reports (the EEP Spending Reports) | Description: The Recipient shall furnish to theAssociation every semester starting six months after the Effective Date, regular reports (the Eligible Expenditure Program SpendingReports) prepared in accordance with the provisions of the Project Regional Operations Manual and the additional instructionsreferred to in Section IV.A.1 of this Schedule. | Frequency: Semiannual

Cote d'Ivoire: Finance Agreement: Verification of DLIs | Description: The Recipient shall, by no later than two months after theEffective date, appoint external monitoring and evaluation experts (“Independent Verifiers”) to act as third-party verifiers of theproper fulfillment of DLIs as set forth in Schedule 4 of the Financing Agreement”. | Frequency: Semiannual

Finance Agreement :Maintain institutional arrangements for the Project | Description :Each participating country shall maintainthroughout the project:(a) its Representative in the Steering Committee to provide overall guidance and oversight for the Projectand to participate with at least semi-annual meetings.(b) the National Review Committee to hold semi-annual reviews of performanceand implementation support.(c) the Implementation Team to run the day-to-day management | Frequency :Semiannual

Finance Agreement: Maintain institutional arrangements for the Project | Description: Each participating country shall maintainthroughout the project: (a) its Representative in the Steering Committee to provide overall guidance and oversight for the Projectand to participate with at least semi-annual meetings. (b) the National Review Committee to hold semi-annual reviews ofperformance and implementation support. (c) the Implementation Team to run the day-to-day management | Frequency: Semiannual

Finance Agreement: Prepare an annual work plan | Description: The Recipient shall each calendar year, prepare, in cooperation withthe Participating University (ies) and furnish to the Association, a program of activities and budget. | Frequency: Yearly

Finance Agreement: Recruitment of an external auditor | Description :(applicable to all countries)The Recipient shall, not laterthan six months after the Effective Date, recruit an external independent auditor, under terms of reference and with qualificationsacceptable to the Bank. | Due Date :31-Dec-2014

Finance Agreement: Regular reports (the EEP Spending Reports) | Description: The Recipient shall furnish to the Association everysemester starting six months after the Effective Date, regular reports (the Eligible Expenditure Program Spending Reports) preparedin accordance with the provisions of the Project Regional Operations Manual and the additional instructions referred to in SectionIV.A.1 of this Schedule. | Frequency: Semiannual

Finance Agreement: Verification of DLIs | Description :(applicable to all countries except The Gambia) The Recipient shall, by nolater than two months after the Effective date, appoint external monitoring and evaluation experts (“Independent Verifiers”) to actas third-party verifiers of the proper fulfillment of DLIs as set forth in Schedule 4 of the Financing Agreement”. | Frequency:Semiannual
